# AI Project Context – Delivery Gjilan (Mobile Customer)

This project is an Expo / React Native app using Expo Router.
Follow this structure strictly.

---

## 🧠 Architecture Overview

Screens (app/)
→ Hooks (logic & data)
→ GraphQL operations / lib
→ Store (global state if needed)

Screens must stay thin.

---

## 📦 App Navigation (Expo Router)

app/
├─ _layout.tsx        → Root layout
├─ index.tsx          → Entry screen
├─ login.tsx
├─ signup.tsx
├─ create-transaction.tsx
└─ (tabs)/
   ├─ _layout.tsx     → Tabs layout
   ├─ home.tsx
   ├─ add.tsx
   ├─ analytics.tsx
   └─ profile.tsx

Rules:
- Files in `app/` are SCREENS only
- No business logic here
- No API calls here

---

## 🪝 Hooks (PRIMARY WORK AREA)

hooks/

Examples:
- useBusinesses.ts
- useOrders.ts
- useProducts.ts
- useAuth.ts

Rules:
- All data fetching & mutations live here
- Hooks may talk to store & GraphQL
- Create new hooks for new features
- Hooks must be reusable

---

## 🧾 GraphQL Operations

graphql/operations/
├─ auth/
├─ businesses/
├─ orders/
├─ products/

Rules:
- GraphQL documents ONLY
- No React code
- One domain per folder
- Do not duplicate backend schema

---

## 🧱 State Management

store/

Rules:
- Global state only (auth, cart, preferences)
- No API calls inside store
- Hooks coordinate store + API

---

## 🧩 UI Components

components/

Rules:
- Dumb / presentational components
- Receive props only
- No fetching, no global state

---

## 🌍 Localization

localization/

Rules:
- All user-facing text should go through i18n
- Do not hardcode strings in screens

---

## 🚫 Do NOT Touch

- metro.config.js
- babel.config.js
- nativewind-env.d.ts
- tsconfig.json
- Generated or config files unless asked

---

## 🧭 How to Execute Tasks

When given a task:

1. Identify feature/domain
2. Create or update a hook
3. Use existing GraphQL operations or add new ones
4. Connect hook to screen
5. Keep screen minimal

---

## ❓ When Unsure

Ask ONE clear question.
Do NOT guess or invent structure.
